SIMPLE: tabular
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tabular
<hw>Tab"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tabularis</ets>, fr. <ets>tabula</ets> a board, table. See
<er>Table</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the form of, or pertaining to, a
table (in any of the uses of the word).</def> Specifically: --⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having a flat surface; <as>as, a <ex>tabular</ex>
rock</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Formed into a succession of flakes;
laminated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nodules . . . that are <qex>tabular</qex> and plated.</q>
<rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>Set in squares.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>Arranged in a schedule; <as>as, <ex>tabular</ex>
statistics</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(e)</sd> <def>Derived from, or computed by, the use of tables;
<as>as, <ex>tabular</ex> right ascension</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tabular difference</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>the
difference between two consecutive numbers in a table, sometimes printed
in its proper place in the table.</cd> -- <col><b>Tabular spar</b></col>
<fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>wollastonite.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tabularization</ent>⟦br⟧
